##Exclusive | first group of Shanghai to Hubei Medical Team leader Zheng Junhua: critically ill patients have accumulated some experience

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

On the afternoon of February 4, the Xinmin Weekly connected with Zheng Junhua, the leader of the first shanghai-hubei medical aid team, the temporary general secretary of the Party branch and the deputy director of the Shanghai First People's Hospital, who was on the front line, to understand the first group of shanghai-hubei medical team in Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, the specific situation, but also to clarify the current community for the medical team security concerns.
Zheng said that after more than 10 days of running-in, the medical team has reached a basic tacit understanding and formed a team spirit. Everyone is working hard at present, hoping to treat patients more and better and reduce the death rate. The medical staff's protection is the most important, because only the medical staff is healthy, can treat more patients, he hopes everyone can come safely, safe return to Shanghai.

On the afternoon of February 4, the Xinmin Weekly connected with Zheng Junhua, the leader of the first shanghai-hubei medical aid team, the temporary general secretary of the Party branch and the deputy director of the Shanghai First People's Hospital, who was on the front line, to understand the first group of shanghai-hubei medical team in Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, the specific situation, but also to clarify the current community for the medical team security concerns.

Zheng said that after more than 10 days of running-in, the medical team has reached a basic tacit understanding and formed a team spirit. Everyone is working hard at present, hoping to treat patients more and better and reduce the death rate. The medical staff's protection is the most important, because only the medical staff is healthy, can treat more patients, he hopes everyone can come safely, safe return to Shanghai.

By Zhou Jie

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xinmin: It has been nearly two weeks since the first Shanghai Hubei Medical Team went to Wuhan. Do we have some experience in understanding the disease and the treatment strategy?

Zheng: We started on New Year's Eve. It's been almost 12 days today. When we arrived, the team was put through a lot, especially to overcome their fears. However, after more than 10 days of work, medical staff for the diagnosis and treatment of disease has been further understanding, but also accumulated some experience.

Our medical team is responsible for more than 60 patients in two wards on the north second floor and the north third floor of Jinyintan Hospital. As of February 4,4 patients have been cured and discharged. We analyze all the clinical data on a daily basis to determine our treatment options for patients currently in first-line clinical care.

From now on, the proportion of severe cases is probably between 10% and 20% . According to the National Health and construction commission, the mortality rate of patients with new coronary pneumonia in China is 2.1% , and that in Wuhan is higher, 4.9% . As long as 80% of patients "early detection, early reporting, early isolation, early treatment" , can achieve a very good therapeutic effect.

For the confirmed patient, the first thing is to strengthen his immunity; the second is to do some symptomatic treatment. There are some new protocols for drug selection, but further clinical evidence is needed, and we are still looking.

In addition, our medical team is currently treating critically ill patients, there is a very significant performance is obvious lung damage, there is obvious hypoxemia, respiratory failure and accompanied by multiple organ failure. Depending on the patient's medical condition, including Hypoxia, respiratory failure, and severity of respiratory failure, respiratory support may be used, it includes nasal tube oxygen inhalation, high flow oxygen therapy, tracheal intubation, aspiration, non-invasive aspiration, invasive aspiration and even cardiopulmonary resuscitation (ECMO) .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zheng Junhua (second from left) with the first group of discharged patients

Xinmin: Are there enough medical resources at the moment?

Zheng Junhua: the Jinyintan Hospital is currently the largest hospital for the treatment of critically ill patients. It also brings together experts and elites from the Department of aspiration and the Department of Critical Care Medicine in the country at present. We have three medical teams from different places to support us, they include the Shanghai medical team, the Beijing medical team, the Fujian Medical Team (which succeeded the army medical university medical team) , the Wuhan People's Hospital, the Tongji Hospital and the Xiehe Hospital, as well as a national team of experts in critical care. WE'RE GONNA face this disease together, and we're GONNA be part of the cure.

With the current national academician level experts, as well as experts in various sectors of the COVID-19, we are able to better grasp the characteristics of prevention and control, and continue to understand the disease. We are also studying and implementing the treatment plan of "Four anti-two balance" proposed by academician Li Lanjuan for the treatment of critically ill patients and the fifth edition of national diagnostic and therapeutic guidelines. The negative-turning characteristics and changes of nucleic acid test in our medical team also provide reference for us to treat patients and judge their conditions and do better prevention and control work. For example, the number of susceptible people, previously thought to be mostly older people with multiple underlying diseases, has increased in parallel with the number of children and pregnant women.

At present, the Wuhan Government also classifies the "four categories of people" into intensive care and isolation, especially the construction of shelter hospitals, which I believe can have a more positive effect on disease control than home-based isolation. After all, most families don't know much about the medical aspects of disease prevention and control, especially disinfection, so Wuhan's move should be key to the development of the epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xinmin Weekly: How are the staff of our medical team working at the moment? How do you ensure that they are able to work effectively over the long term?

Zheng Junhua: our medical team for the treatment of diseases, is constantly accumulating experience, we are also constantly improving our process, to find gaps, fill gaps, continuous improvement. We need to recognize that the epidemic is long term, complex and severe, and we need to protect our health care workers adequately and have the energy and energy to face such challenges.

On January 27, the Shanghai Municipal Health and Health Commission added 50 nursing members to our staff, 35 of whom were transferred to other wards of Jinyintan Hospital, and the other 15 were integrated into our management and were responsible for the rotation of the two wards. Because there are no nurses in the ward, our nurses are not only in charge of medical care, but also life care. So as our nursing force has increased, we have adjusted the working hours of the hardest nursing posts on the front line to four-hour shifts, in the hope that after such an adjustment, the medical staff will be able to go to the battlefield, and get more rest at the end of the day.

In addition, we have made some efforts to ensure that our medical staff can work efficiently and effectively in the long term. We have established the Party's General Branch, which requires Party members to take the first line of fighting against the epidemic, and to give full play to the vanguard and exemplary role of Party members and the role of Party branches as battle bastions. This time, among the 136 members, there were 59 party members and one reserve party member. We held a meeting of all Party members. During the Party class, there were eight active party members on the spot who asked to join the party in the front line, by now, more than 40 comrades have applied to join the party.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the evening of January 28, the Shanghai Medical Team for Hubei Province held the first meeting of all Party members

In addition, all of our medical staff are physically and mentally healthy.

Let me give you two examples. These two days, there are some birthday team members, we together to give them a simple ceremony, a small birthday, everyone warm heart, also a little relax. Also, because some of the lesbians had long hair when we first came here, it wasn't good for protection, so one of our lesbians volunteered to cut everyone's hair. As a team, we respect each other, care for each other, understand each other and support each other. After a period of running-in, we should say a basic tacit understanding of the stage.

In terms of material support, we have received strong support from the Shanghai Municipal Party Committee, the municipal government, the Health Commission and the Shenkang Hospital Development Center, especially the hospitals where our team members are located, we are also very grateful to the enterprises, organizations, foundations and individuals from all over the country for their sympathy and support. In this, we can also say one thing, that is, the Guangming Group has sent vegetables, grain, milk and so on to all our family members in Shanghai. The family members of our team members are also very moved, very grateful, there are also the Shanghai Medical Union, Hema Shengxian, Meituan, Greenland and so on, I can not say all at once, in short, in the community's concern, our team members are very confident to overcome the epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Feb. 2, medical workers from the Shanghai Hubei Medical Aid team video linked with Li Qiang, the party secretary of the city

Xinmin Weekly: The epidemic is still developing, and our medical staff have been working for nearly two weeks. When can we expect to have a rotation and a rest?

Zheng: We don't think it's necessary yet. Since we have just arrived, we have also made up our minds. Now that we are here and have been dispatched by the Shanghai municipal government, we must do a good job. We have not thought of taking a rest in the future, and we should not take a rest at this time. We should still fight in the front line, and our team is just beginning to understand and understand the relevant experience of the epidemic.

The new medical team has a running-in process, we now form a team of cooperation, we should do is more time to treat patients. Chen Erzhen, the deputy director of Ruijin Hospital and the leader of the third group of medical teams in Hubei, said: We will not pay back until we break the Loulan Kingdom. In fact, this is our idea, we will fulfill our mission.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xinmin Weekly: What was your biggest personal experience during your two weeks working in Wuhan?

Zheng Junhua: I have four feelings in my heart, very deep.

My biggest feeling is that I really feel the strong leadership of our Party and the superiority of our socialist system, and I have even more set up four consciousnesses, four self-confidence, and two resolute maintenance.

Wuhan now has more than 8,000 medical team members from 29 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions, as well as medical teams from the military. No other country has the same resolute ability to implement as China.

Secondly, the current system of prevention and control against the epidemic is in the process of forming. We, who are in the midst of history, do indeed feel the efficiency of our government. At the beginning, there may be a process of understanding about the epidemic, but now the fight against the epidemic as a most important, the most important work.

The local government people I spoke to, they did their best to meet our needs. In particular, it provides full logistical support for our accommodation, living, commuting and safety.

Third, I have also fully felt the spirit of our national medical workers. In the national call, no hospital, no medical staff is a retreat, which also reflects the medical staff's sense of mission, sense of responsibility as if the epidemic is an order.

The fourth point is that I fully feel the Chinese culture, "one party in difficulty, eight support" spirit. Many businesses, teams, and individuals have done their best to provide support after the outbreak. Many overseas Chinese and overseas students have tried their best to help us with medical supplies, especially N95 masks, medical protective clothing, goggles and so on. We all together to fight the epidemic, Wuhan, is not a isolated city, the people of the country support you, this, I feel very deep.
